<HEADLINE>
<P>
KEEPING RTD BUSES ON TIME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hooray! Someone wrote an article, not just a letter, about the awful RTD 
service. I don't think the average bus rider has the ambition to write a 
letter; riders are too tired from standing in buses or waiting for one. 
</P>
<P>
There is a printed sign in all buses that says it is unlawful to stand in the 
stairwell. Most of the drivers don't seem to pay attention to it. Since they 
cut down on the service on June 25 it seems they can't say to wait for the next 
bus because who knows when there will be another one. 
</P>
<P>
I hope Wishart's article will wake up some of the officials to improve the bus 
service. 
</P>
<P>
MARGE WALLACE 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
