<HEADLINE>
<P>
KEEPING RTD BUSES ON TIME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I am a bus operator working out of Division 5 in South-Central Los Angeles. 
This slam at my fellow operators angers me. I love my job and what I do. But 
I'm sure that the author wants answers not explanations. We stress teamwork on 
the job and most of the time it works as it was intended. 
</P>
<P>
Sir, this is a large city, a first-rate city with a first-rate transit system. 
With so many people unable to afford a car, let alone the necessary insurance 
costs that go with owning that car, we provide a lifeline for seniors, 
students, shoppers and working people. We're their wheels and we really do the 
best we can at all times. And it isn't always easy. 
</P>
<P>
GEORGE STAFFORD 
</P>
<P>
Manhattan Beach 
</P>
