<HEADLINE>
<P>
FLYING CONTINENTAL HOLDS OFF NO MARKER FOR OAK TREE VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Flying Continental, owned by Jack Kent Cooke, got a battle from No Marker 
through the stretch but prevailed by a neck in Thursday's $60,000 feature race 
of the Oak Tree meeting at Santa Anita. 
</P>
<P>
The top two finishers ran in tandem throughout the 1 1/16-mile race, sitting 
just off the early pace of Mi Preferido and Prove Splendid. 
</P>
<P>
Flying Continental and No Marker moved together to take the lead at the top of 
the stretch and raced head-to-head from there. 
</P>
<P>
Flying Continental, ridden by Chris McCarron and trained by Jay Robbins, was 
clocked in 1:41 4/5 and returned $5.80, $2.80 and $2.40. No Marker paid $4.40 
and $3.20. 
</P>
<P>
Gaucho Alerta, who trailed the field by 12 lengths on the backstretch, finished 
strongly to take third as the pacesetters faded in the final quarter-mile. 
Gaucho Alerta paid $3.60. 
</P>
<P>
It was Flying Continental's first victory since the Santa Catalina Stakes at 
Santa Anita in February. 
</P>
