</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
T-Bill Rates Fall: Interest rates on 52-week Treasury bills fell at the latest 
action to the lowest level since July. The Treasury sold $9.8 billion of new 
bills at an average discount rate of 7.35%, down from 7.61% at the last auction 
on Sept. 21. The rates were the lowest since July 27, when the one-year bills 
sold for 7.22%. The new discount rate understates the actual return to 
investors -- 7.90%, with a $10,000 bill selling for $9,256.80. 
</P>
</TEXT>
