<HEADLINE>
<P>
KCBS BUYS REMAINING TICKETS, PUTTING RAM GAME ON TV SUNDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LARRY STEWART 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles will get a Ram-Raider doubleheader on television Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
The Rams announced Thursday that their game against the New Orleans Saints on 
Sunday at Anaheim Stadium was a sellout before the 1 p.m. deadline for lifting 
the television blackout. 
</P>
<P>
A Ram spokesman said KCBS, which will televise the game here, bought the 
remaining tickets. The spokesman did not say how many tickets remained, nor did 
a spokeswoman for KCBS. 
</P>
<P>
Reportedly, about 5,000 tickets were still unsold Thursday morning. 
</P>
<P>
The game announcers for the 1 p.m. telecast on Channel 2 will be Steve 
Zabriskie and Hank Stram. 
</P>
<P>
KCBS was originally scheduled to show the New York Giant-San Diego Charger game 
from San Diego. 
</P>
<P>
The Ram-Saint telecast will follow the Raiders' game against the Eagles at 
Philadelphia, which will be on Channel 4 at 10 a.m. Joel Meyers and Paul 
Maguire will report. 
</P>
<P>
This is first local telecast of a Ram home game this season. Even Eric 
Dickerson's return with the Indianapolis Colts on Sept. 17 wasn't televised 
locally. The game didn't sell out, but even if it had, it couldn't have been 
televised because of a scheduling snafu. LARRY STEWART 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
FOOTBALL GAMES; LOS ANGELES RAMS (FOOTBALL TEAM); NEW ORLEANS SAINTS (FOOTBALL 
TEAM); TICKETS; TELEVISION BROADCASTS; KCBS (TELEVISION STATION) 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
