<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE NEXT STEP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Washington-based National Endowment for the Arts is awaiting a review of 
the Bay Area arts situation by a senior staff member who happened to be in San 
Francisco at the time of the quake. The endowment said it was prepared to offer 
disaster relief funds to arts institutions that sustained specific losses of 
such things as vehicles, costumes and buildings. Affected organizations can 
contact the endowment program office that oversees their disciplines. The 
endowment's general telephone number is (202) 682-5400. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
