Thursday over portion of 9,200-acre brush fire near Ortega Highway in South 
Orange County. The flames spewed ash as far north as Long Beach. GARY AMBROSE / 
Los Angeles Times; Map, 3-COUNTY FIRE. A brush fire burned more than 9,200 
acres over two days starting at Camp Pendleton in San Diego County and then 
into the canyons of south Orange and Riverside counties., Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
