<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SADDLEBACK / SOUTH BEACH; 
</P>
<P>
MISSION VIEJO; 
</P>
<P>
ANTI-DRUG FAIR PLANNED FOR OCT. 28 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Organizers of an anti-drug fair predict more than 1,000 people will show up for 
the culmination of the second annual Red Ribbon Week at Saddleback College on 
Oct. 28. 
</P>
<P>
The all-day event is part of a national anti-drug campaign run by Parents for 
Drug-Free Use. Festivities will include a soap-box derby, pancake breakfast, 
games and live entertainment. 
</P>
<P>
The Red Ribbon campaign was inspired by the death of federal agent Enrique 
Camarena at the hands of drug traffickers, Chariton said. 
</P>
<P>
Last year's event attracted more than 500 people to Saddleback College. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
