<P>
CITY TO SEEK MORE FAMILY RESTAURANTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LINDA HICKMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fed up with fast food, the City Council has voted to adopt "an aggressive 
marketing approach" to attract more family restaurants to the city. 
</P>
<P>
A report by Community Development Director Phillip S. Paxton this week said 
that while the city is saturated with fast-food and takeout establishments, it 
can accommodate more sit-down restaurants. 
</P>
<P>
"From an economic and demographic point of view, Yorba Linda can support 38% 
more restaurants than the average (city) in the United States," Paxton said. 
</P>
<P>
Although the motion was passed unanimously, the council did not reach agreement 
on how it will attract new restaurants to the city. LINDA HICKMAN 
