<HEADLINE>
<P>
MEMBERS SOUGHT FOR ADVISORY PANELS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
FULLERTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
There are openings on several city committees and commissions that advise the 
City Council on civic issues. 
</P>
<P>
Positions are open on the Planning Commission, Community Services Commission, 
Airport Noise and Safety Committee, Energy Resource and Management Committee, 
Library Board of Trustees and two redevelopment project area committees. 
</P>
<P>
The Planning Commission reviews applications for building site plans, 
conditional-use permits, variances and zoning permits. Decisions by commission 
members help shape the future look of Fullerton. It meets two nights a month. 
</P>
<P>
The other commissions and committees meet monthly or less often. 
</P>
<P>
Applications for the openings may be picked up at City Hall, 303 W. 
Commonwealth Ave. The deadline to return applications is Nov. 1. Call (714) 
738-6311 for information. 
</P>
