<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE BAY AREA QUAKE; 
</P>
<P>
5:04 P.M.; 
</P>
<P>
A TIME WHEN LIVES CHANGED; 
</P>
<P>
TALES OF THE QUAKE: DEATH, HEROES AND LUCK ; 
</P>
<P>
DEATH COMES ON CHURCH STEEPLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL CONNELLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Curtis Currin, a 24-year-old systems engineer from Redwood City, was working on 
a church steeple at St. Joseph's Seminary in Los Altos when the earthquake 
struck. 
</P>
<P>
The steeple collapsed and he fell with it, suffering traumatic injuries when 
the structure crushed him. He died about an hour later. MICHAEL CONNELLY 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
